{{flavour|A potion which eliminates your control over your own body.}}

Quaffing a '''potion of paralysis''' [[Paralysis|paralyzes]] your character for 1d6 + 1 turns. Using it in the middle of a fight (because you've run out of options and are resorting to unidentified potion roulette) will turn you into a punching bag for monsters.

{{crawlquote|''You suddenly lose the ability to move!''}}

==History==
Potions of paralysis were removed in [[0.15]].

Prior to [[0.12]], potions of paralysis were not entirely useless. When combined with the [[Evaporate]] spell, they would create [[Mephitic Cloud]]s.
